that Mordor somehow got himself shot.

251
00:12:44,765 --> 00:12:46,431
And so I'd like to apologize.

252
00:12:46,599 --> 00:12:47,622
That's okay.

253
00:12:47,747 --> 00:12:49,395
I'm just glad you're rid of him.

254
00:12:49,520 --> 00:12:51,728
That guy was
a self-absorbed dill-hole.

255
00:12:52,407 --> 00:12:55,649
"Ooh, I'm Mordor. I think
all men are in love with me."

256
00:12:55,817 --> 00:12:58,360
- I mean, seriously, what a doofus.
- We made up.

257
00:13:00,560 --> 00:13:01,440
Oh, good,

258
00:13:02,036 --> 00:13:04,950
'cause now I can stop pretending
I don't like him.

259
00:13:05,118 --> 00:13:07,318
He had an affair, and I shot him.

260
00:13:07,748 --> 00:13:09,508
So we decided to call in.

261
00:13:09,932 --> 00:13:11,573
Plus, I found out why he did it.

262
00:13:11,698 --> 00:13:13,577
Apparently somebody suggested

263
00:13:13,702 --> 00:13:16,721
- that he ease up on our relationship.
- I didn't mean...

264
00:13:16,846 --> 00:13:17,671
It was you?

265
00:13:20,785 --> 00:13:22,650
- What was me?
- My god, Ted.

266
00:13:22,775 --> 00:13:25,571
You don't tell a man like Mordor
to be less passionate.

267
00:13:25,696 --> 00:13:27,695
It's like telling Gandhi
to be less...

268
00:13:27,820 --> 00:13:28,965
Whatever he was.

269
00:13:29,228 --> 00:13:30,100
Thin.

270
00:13:30,268 --> 00:13:31,469
Your job wasn't done.

271
00:13:31,594 --> 00:13:34,252
You were falling asleep
at work with your eyes open.

272
00:13:34,498 --> 00:13:35,890
What if they dried out?

273
00:13:36,015 --> 00:13:38,442
They would've lost their luster.
I was worried.

274
00:13:39,358 --> 00:13:42,362
I don't need you or anyone else
interfering in my life.

275
00:13:42,640 --> 00:13:45,449
You're responsible for
my boyfriend screwing around.

276
00:13:45,574 --> 00:13:47,139
You're the one who shot him.

277
00:13:47,660 --> 00:13:48,618
In my mind.

278
00:13:49,150 --> 00:13:51,250
And then, you call him a dill-hole

279
00:13:51,545 --> 00:13:52,672
right to his face.

280
00:13:52,797 --> 00:13:54,512
- No.
- In my mind.

281
00:13:55,692 --> 00:13:58,070
I think you and I need
a little distance from each other.

282
00:13:58,385 --> 00:13:59,501
That's a good idea.

283
00:14:00,026 --> 00:14:01,131
I'll go to my office.

284
00:14:01,299 --> 00:14:02,299
Actually,

285
00:14:02,834 --> 00:14:04,831
I was thinking
a little more distance.

286
00:14:05,720 --> 00:14:09,558
<i>And so Veronica sent me down
to the ridiculously tiny office.</i>

287
00:14:45,007 --> 00:14:46,857
This is not as bad as I imagined.

288
00:14:46,982 --> 00:14:49,012
Your chair and desk look gigantic
it's cool.

289
00:14:49,448 --> 00:14:52,307
Plus, it would be impossible
to lose anything in here.

290
00:14:52,806 --> 00:14:54,100
It's all great.

291
00:14:54,322 --> 00:14:56,812
So what's up, fellas?
'cause I'm busy getting into my chair.

292
00:14:57,070 --> 00:14:58,070
We're...

293
00:14:58,257 --> 00:14:59,731
unhappy about something.

294
00:15:00,411 --> 00:15:01,399
Is it the coat?

295
00:15:01,567 --> 00:15:03,947
I worked my ass off yesterday
to get that thing.

296
00:15:04,072 --> 00:15:06,196
I can't tell you exactly
what's going on.

297
00:15:06,364 --> 00:15:08,031
I'm in trouble
as it is with Veronica.

298
00:15:08,199 --> 00:15:11,461
But the coat may not be something
you want to work extra hard to get.

299
00:15:12,245 --> 00:15:14,098
It's so beautiful.

300
00:15:14,321 --> 00:15:18,045
Only because you think
it means something, which it may not.

301
00:15:18,431 --> 00:15:20,382
- I know what's going on.
- We're confused.

302
00:15:20,507 --> 00:15:22,209
That's exactly what's happening.

303
00:15:26,288 --> 00:15:29,194
I can't believe
you trashed Veronica's boyfriend.

304
00:15:30,443 --> 00:15:33,014
You never trash the boyfriend.
What if they get back together?

305
00:15:33,182 --> 00:15:34,571
I don't care anymore.

306
00:15:34,696 --> 00:15:35,696
I'm out.

307
00:15:35,893 --> 00:15:38,520
I am done getting in the middle
of Veronica's relationship.

308
00:15:38,688 --> 00:15:41,001
Because believe it or not,
there's an office smaller,

309
00:15:41,126 --> 00:15:42,942
and you have to share it
with someone.

310
00:15:43,151 --> 00:15:45,618
You should be out,
you know nothing about relationships.

311
00:15:45,820 --> 00:15:47,753
I don't know anything
about relationships?

312
00:15:48,132 --> 00:15:50,011
It's because
of your relationship geniusness

313
00:15:50,136 --> 00:15:51,866
that I'm stuck
in Polly Pocket's house.

314
00:15:52,034 --> 00:15:53,495
- We should go.
- We want to go.

315
00:15:53,620 --> 00:15:57,446
Thanks to me? I never told you
to tell her that her boyfriend sucks.

316
00:15:57,571 --> 00:15:59,892
I wouldn't have kept talking about
her sucky boyfriend

317
00:16:00,084 --> 00:16:02,914
- if you hadn't kept bringing him up.
- I had to bring it up,

318
00:16:03,039 --> 00:16:06,006
because you think relationships
are all about what the guy wants.

319
00:16:06,131 --> 00:16:07,788
And by the way, genius,

320
00:16:07,913 --> 00:16:10,383
Polly Pockets doesn't live in a house,
but in a clamshell!

321
00:16:10,508 --> 00:16:12,382
- I know where she lives.
- Really?

322
00:16:12,507 --> 00:16:15,640
Because I think you know less about
Polly Pockets than relationships.

323
00:16:17,842 --> 00:16:18,894
That's better.

324
00:16:19,228 --> 00:16:21,732
So if the coat's not a reward something good},
then that must mean...

325
00:16:22,336 --> 00:16:24,733
It's a punishment
for doing something bad.

326
00:16:24,983 --> 00:16:26,364
It's like a scarlet letter.

327
00:16:26,489 --> 00:16:28,737
Only it's worse,
because it covers the body in shame.

328
00:16:29,694 --> 00:16:31,500
So why'd the company give it to me?

329
00:16:31,857 --> 00:16:35,151
You did break the dieoxolater
defibulation splung manifold last week,

330
00:16:35,276 --> 00:16:37,039
and that sucka is expensive.

331
00:16:37,442 --> 00:16:40,457
If I hadn't tried to protect my eyes,
I might have been able to save it.

332
00:16:40,857 --> 00:16:42,303
Stupid reflexes.

333
00:16:43,445 --> 00:16:46,365
<i>The next morning, I checked in
to see if I could come back.</i>

334
00:16:46,570 --> 00:16:48,220
Good morning, sunshine.

335
00:16:48,758 --> 00:16:49,758
Not yet.

336
00:16:53,262 --> 00:16:54,612
<i>And in the lab...</i>

337
00:16:58,032 --> 00:16:59,976
It was in my locker this morning.

338
00:17:01,068 --> 00:17:03,045
I worked so hard yesterday

339
00:17:03,170 --> 00:17:05,118
to avoid this exact thing.

340
00:17:05,950 --> 00:17:07,682
All we can do is buckle down

341
00:17:07,807 --> 00:17:09,857
and push ourselves even harder.

342
00:17:11,632 --> 00:17:13,412
I hope Veronica forgives me soon,

343
00:17:13,537 --> 00:17:15,617
because I really like doing this...

344
00:17:17,039 --> 00:17:19,037
Which I totally took
for granted before.

345
00:17:22,500 --> 00:17:23,521
What the hell?

346
00:17:23,646 --> 00:17:26,169
Ted! I thought
you were working out of the basement.

347
00:17:26,337 --> 00:17:28,136
I'm getting papers.
What are you doing?

348
00:17:28,371 --> 00:17:29,371
This is...

349
00:17:29,957 --> 00:17:30,757
Tiffany.

350
00:17:31,133 --> 00:17:32,834
Thank you.
See,

351
00:17:33,242 --> 00:17:34,427
I figured it out.

352
00:17:34,595 --> 00:17:36,458
I hurt Veronica by fooling around,

353
00:17:36,583 --> 00:17:39,140
but then she shooted me with a speargun,
that reset the relationship.

354
00:17:39,382 --> 00:17:40,898
So I can fool around again,

355
00:17:41,023 --> 00:17:44,419
as long as I'm willing to let Veronica
hurt me again, which I am,

356
00:17:44,544 --> 00:17:47,315
'cause I like promiscuous sex
far more than I dislike pain.

357
00:17:48,321 --> 00:17:51,238
You know, I didn't want to get involved
in Veronica's personal life,

358
00:17:51,363 --> 00:17:54,406
but now I'm glad I did,
because you don't deserve her.

359
00:17:55,132 --> 00:17:58,743
She is smart, and beautiful,
and confident... Wildly fun in bed...

360
00:17:59,745 --> 00:18:02,872
I've been there. She is
the whole package. You're just a jerk.

361
00:18:03,131 --> 00:18:05,750
And, yes, a mammoth dill-hole.

362
00:18:05,946 --> 00:18:07,196
All right, Ted.

363
00:18:07,620 --> 00:18:08,455
Let's go.

364
00:18:08,818 --> 00:18:11,698
You started this whole thing,
and you insult me in front of Tiffany.

365
00:18:12,504 --> 00:18:14,926
- Let's get this over with.
- I won't fight you, you loon.

366
00:18:15,094 --> 00:18:15,945
Loon?

367
00:18:16,071 --> 00:18:18,104
Could a loon do this?

368
00:18:24,448 --> 00:18:25,979
I think a loon would do that.

369
00:18:26,147 --> 00:18:27,981
It's called quad-dela-ron-sha.

370
00:18:29,693 --> 00:18:33,150
It's an ancient peruvian martial art
involving forceful, repeated slapping.

371
00:18:34,319 --> 00:18:35,794
I'm not gonna fight you.

372
00:18:39,257 --> 00:18:40,758
Wait.
Yes, I'll fight you.

373
00:18:42,262 --> 00:18:43,304
What the hell?

374
00:18:44,345 --> 00:18:46,374
It's like you have
a hundred fingers.

375
00:18:48,863 --> 00:18:49,963
Go get help!

376
00:18:54,757 --> 00:18:56,154
Quad-dela-ron-sha...

377
00:18:56,279 --> 00:18:58,136
It's impossible to defend against.

378
00:18:58,705 --> 00:19:00,180
It's why Peru was never conquered.

379
00:19:00,592 --> 00:19:02,015
Didn't the spanish conquer Peru?

380
00:19:02,319 --> 00:19:03,946
Yes, but then they left quickly.

381
00:19:04,071 --> 00:19:05,793
In fact, quad-dela-ron-sha means:

382
00:19:05,918 --> 00:19:07,896
"Leave,
or we'll start with the slapping."

383
00:19:08,644 --> 00:19:10,857
Did Mordor tell you this?
'cause it's not on Google.

384
00:19:12,068 --> 00:19:13,868
Maybe that was also a lie.

385
00:19:14,431 --> 00:19:15,653
I'm through with him.

386
00:19:17,603 --> 00:19:18,990
{\Listen, }I'm sorry about everything.

387
00:19:20,608 --> 00:19:21,756
You stood up for me.

388
00:19:21,881 --> 00:19:23,753
No one's ever done that before.

389
00:19:26,821 --> 00:19:27,821
Thank you.

390
00:19:30,007 --> 00:19:32,201
<i>Maybe it's impossible
to keep your personal life</i>

391
00:19:32,326 --> 00:19:34,173
<i>completely separate from work,</i>

392
00:19:34,382 --> 00:19:37,109
<i>especially when you care about
the people you work with...</i>

393
00:19:39,387 --> 00:19:40,780
<i>And they care about you.</i>

394
00:19:40,905 --> 00:19:41,930
Is he all right?

395
00:19:42,508 --> 00:19:43,431
He's great.

396
00:19:43,599 --> 00:19:46,506
I can't believe he fought
to defend your honor. That is so...

397
00:19:46,686 --> 00:19:48,686
- Hot?
- Actually, It kind of is.

398
00:19:50,114 --> 00:19:52,943
And I told him he didn't know
anything about relationships.

399
00:19:53,068 --> 00:19:55,618
He may not
but he'd sure be good in one.

400
00:20:04,731 --> 00:20:06,013
Again?

401
00:20:07,604 --> 00:20:09,895
What have I done?

402
00:20:10,718 --> 00:20:13,325
<i>{And since I do care about
the people I work with,</i>

403
00:20:13,450 --> 00:20:15,228
<i>I decided to end their suffering.</i>

404
00:20:18,884 --> 00:20:20,632
<i>Since any change helps productivity,</i>

405
00:20:20,757 --> 00:20:22,322
<i>why not make it a positive change</i>

406
00:20:22,447 --> 00:20:24,347
<i>and do something
people can feel good about?</i>

407
00:20:29,350 --> 00:20:30,750
What does it mean?

408
00:20:31,412 --> 00:20:33,507
Maybe we've been asking
too many questions.

409
00:20:34,288 --> 00:20:36,860
Maybe this is the company's equivalent
of sending a dead fish.

